<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/141713a5-c923-46fe-81e6-49f2cad7e598>
        rdf:type            skos:Concept;
        dc:modified         "2025-03-14T12:00:44.313Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        skos:definition     "The difference between the total incoming and total outgoing energy. If this balance is positive, warming occurs; if it is negative, cooling occurs. Averaged over the globe and over long time periods, this balance must be zero. Because the climate system derives virtually all its energy from the Sun, zero balance implies that, globally, the absorbed solar radiation, that is, incoming solar radiation minus reflected solar radiation at the top of the atmosphere and outgoing longwave radiation emitted by the climate system are equal."@en;
        skos:editorialNote  "source:IPCC Glossary AR6";
        skos:inScheme       <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        skos:prefLabel      "Energy balance"@en;
        skos:topConceptOf   <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        gs:revisionNo       1 .

