<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/15776bf2-326b-4c13-9c25-2666b5781dc5>
        rdf:type            skos:Concept;
        dc:modified         "2025-03-14T12:00:44.313Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        skos:definition     "Non-CO2 emissions included in this report are all anthropogenic emissions other than carbon dioxide (CO2) that result in radiative forcing. These include short-lived climate forcers, such as methane (CH4), some fluorinated gases, ozone (O3) precursors, aerosols or aerosol precursors, such as black carbon and sulphur dioxide, respectively, as well as long-lived greenhouse gases, such as nitrous oxide (N2O) or other fluorinated gases. The radiative forcing associated with non-CO2 emissions and changes in surface albedo (e.g., resulting from land-use change) is referred to as non-CO2 radiative forcing."@en;
        skos:editorialNote  "source:IPCC Glossary AR6";
        skos:inScheme       <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        skos:prefLabel      "Non-CO2 emissions and radiative forcing"@en;
        skos:topConceptOf   <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        gs:revisionNo       1 .

