<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/4491509f-5980-4c06-9cd3-d54b6c33f3d4>
        rdf:type           skos:Concept;
        dc:created         "2025-06-03T10:46:28.341Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dc:modified        "2025-06-03T10:55:24.749Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        skos:definition    "Satellite observation refers to the use of satellites to collect data about the Earth and its various subsystems, such as the atmosphere, oceans, and land surfaces. These observations provide valuable information about the Earth's conditions and are made possible by the continuous operations and global coverage of satellites (Sellitto, 2017)."@en;
        skos:historyNote   "P. Sellitto, Chapter 9 - Artificial Neural Networks for Spectral Sensitivity Analysis to Optimize Inversion Algorithms for Satellite-Based Earth Observation: Sulfate Aerosol Observations With High-Resolution Thermal Infrared Sounders,\nEditor(s): George P. Petropoulos, Prashant K. Srivastava,\nSensitivity Analysis in Earth Observation Modelling,\nElsevier, 2017, Pages 161-175,\nISBN 9780128030110,\nhttps://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-12-803011-0.00009-4."@en;
        skos:inScheme      <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        skos:prefLabel     "Satellite observations"@en;
        skos:topConceptOf  <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        gs:revisionNo      4 .

