<http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/e7654a8e-a749-42af-8b79-eb125de32e2d>
        rdf:type           skos:Concept;
        dc:created         "2025-06-10T15:48:00.285Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dc:modified        "2025-06-10T15:50:16.115Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        skos:definition    "Meterological forecasting with local detail, by any method, over a period from the present to six hours ahead, including a detailed description of the present weather (WMO, 2017)."@en;
        skos:historyNote   "WMO (2017) Guidlines for Nowcasting techniques. WMO NO. 1198.\n\nBańbura, Marta, Giannone, Domenico, & Reichlin, Lucrezia. (2012). Nowcasting. In M. P. Clements & D. F. Hendry (Eds.), The Oxford Handbook of Economic Forecasting (pp. 193–224). Oxford University Press. https://doi.org/10.1093/oxfordhb/9780195398649.013.0008"@en;
        skos:inScheme      <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        skos:prefLabel     "Nowcasting"@en;
        skos:scopeNote     "In economics, nowcasting is used to describe the real-time estimation of current economic conditions, such as GDP or inflation, using a variety of high-frequency data sources. It helps policymakers and analysts make timely decisions before official statistics are released. Examples are found in pandemic economic modelling and public health in disease spread; as well as in social science for population trends, migration flows, or unemployment rates (Bańbura et al., 2012)."@en;
        skos:topConceptOf  <http://connectivity-hub.com/terms/>;
        gs:revisionNo      6 .

